wiki.content: "Am I Dreaming" is a song by American record producer Metro Boomin, American rapper ASAP Rocky, and American singer Roisee. It was released through Boominati Worldwide and Republic Records as the second track from Metro's first soundtrack album, which was for the film Spider-Man: Across the Spider-Verse, on June 2, 2023. The three artists wrote the song alongside Mike Dean, Peter Lee Johnson, and Scriptplugg, all of whom produced it with Metro. The song features Roisee singing the chorus and a verse and ASAP Rocky rapping, both from the perspective of Miles Morales from the film Spider-Man: Across the Spider-Verse: "Count up my ones, lacin' up my favorite 1s … Kiss my momma on the forehead 'fore I get the Code Red / And swing by 410, beef patty, cornbread". Musically, the song prominently features a string quartet playing a lilting, mournful melody, which often stands alone without bass or percussion. Roisee’s vocals are also heavily electronically processed. Read more on Last.fm. User-contributed text is available under the Creative Commons By-SA License; additional terms may apply.
